            "type": "text",
            "text": "Multi-Region Architecture for GenAI: The Core Trade-Off"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Multi-region deployment for GenAI inference differs from web applications because the expensive resource \u2014 GPU nodes with model weights loaded \u2014 cannot be spun up in seconds. Every multi-region strategy is a point on a spectrum between cost and recovery speed:"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "bulletList",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Active-active: ",
                    "marks": [
                      {
                        "type": "bold"
                      }
                    ]
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "both regions serve live traffic at all times. Failover is instantaneous (the load balancer simply stops sending to the failed region) but GPU costs are doubled continuously."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Active-passive (warm): ",
                    "marks": [
                      {
                        "type": "bold"
                      }
                    ]
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "one region handles all traffic; the DR region has pods running with weights loaded but serving no requests. Failover takes 5\u201310 minutes (DNS flip + health check validation); cost is ~60% of active-active."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Active-passive (cold): ",
                    "marks": [
                      {
                        "type": "bold"
                      }
                    ]
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "the DR region has no running pods; they are provisioned on demand when a disaster is declared. Failover takes 30\u201390 minutes (GPU allocation + weight loading). Lowest cost but only viable for Tier 3/4 workloads."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          }
        ]
