            "text": "Multi-region failover for GenAI services requires choosing between active-active (instantaneous failover, double GPU cost), warm active-passive (5\u201310 min RTO, ~60% of active-active cost), and cold active-passive (30\u201390 min RTO, minimal standby cost). The right choice depends on the service tier: real-time inference uses active-active or warm standby; batch workloads use cold standby. A provider fallback chain with circuit-breakers handles LLM API failures independently of region failures. Fine-tuned model weights must be audited weekly in the DR region to ensure the warm-standby RTO guarantee is valid. Failback must be executed via weighted traffic shifting \u2014 not a fast DNS flip \u2014 to validate primary health under real load before returning all traffic."
